---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import catalog from '../../../benchmarks/catalog.json';
import {catalogEvidence,frameworks} from '../../../scripts/catalog-evidence.mjs';
const groups=[['Core',['select','button','dialog','popover','checkbox','switch']],['Navigation',['tabs','menu-bar','sidebar','breadcrumbs','table-of-contents']],['Forms',['field','input','input-group','input-area','sensitive-input','clipboard-text']],['Data / Presentational',['badge','banner','surface','layer-card','grid','grid-item','loader','meter','empty','label','link','text','cloudflare-logo','code','table']],['Selection / Command / Date',['radio','autocomplete','combobox','command-palette','date-picker','date-range-picker','dropdown-menu','toasty','pagination']]];
const {components,nativeVue,legacyVue,totals}=catalogEvidence(catalog);
const byId=Object.fromEntries(components.map(c=>[c.id,c]));
const labels={react:'R',vue:'V',svelte:'Sv',solid:'So'};
const ms=value=>`${Number(value).toLocaleString(undefined,{maximumFractionDigits:1})} ms`;
const kb=value=>`${(Number(value)/1024).toLocaleString(undefined,{maximumFractionDigits:1})} kB`;
---
<Layout title="Kumo compiler evidence catalog">
<header class="hero"><p class="eyebrow">Kumo 2.5.2 · evidence catalog</p><h1>Canonical React in, normalized framework surfaces out</h1><p>Kumo starts from the Kumo React components as its canonical inputs. Normalization captures their structure, states, semantics, and behavior in a framework-neutral form; the current catalog then exercises React, Vue, Svelte, and Solid output surfaces.</p></header>
<section class="notice" aria-labelledby="limitation"><h2 id="limitation">Current output status and limitation</h2><p><strong>{nativeVue.length}/{components.length} Vue outputs are framework-native.</strong> The other <strong>{legacyVue.length}/{components.length}</strong> are legacy generated HTML/lookalike family outputs pending migration. A passing visual proof is not a claim that those legacy panels are idiomatic Vue components, nor that every React API has been translated.</p><p>React is the canonical source surface. Vue, Svelte, and Solid are supported proof surfaces: generated runtime pages used to test observable parity. They are evidence fixtures, not a general production-support or source-fidelity guarantee.</p></section>
<section><h2>What “proved” means here</h2><p>The exact catalog gates are: all four runtime routes build; server-rendered markup and expected semantic/ARIA state are present; framework hydration source and hydrated DOM are present where the family proof requires them; required interaction/state tokens pass family-specific checks; screenshots are non-empty and their SHA-256 pixels match across React, Vue, Svelte, and Solid; selected proofs also require repeated dev/production render hashes to match. Bundle bytes are read from each built JavaScript asset. Build milliseconds and bundle bytes below are measured values recorded in <code>benchmarks/catalog.json</code>, not estimates.</p><div class="totals">{frameworks.map(f=><div><strong>{f}</strong><span>{ms(totals[f].meanBuildMs)} mean build</span><span>{kb(totals[f].bundleBytes)} catalog JS total</span></div>)}</div></section>
<section><h2>How to read the evidence</h2><p>The root is the single catalog. Every row links to a component subpage and reports its four framework measurements inline. Measurements describe these checked-in proof fixtures on the recorded catalog source commit <code>{catalog.source.commit}</code>; they are not application-wide performance forecasts. Pixel equality does not prove accessibility, behavioral completeness, source quality, or equivalent runtime internals.</p></section>
{groups.map(([family,ids])=><section class="family"><h2>{family}</h2><div class="table-wrap"><table><thead><tr><th>Component</th><th>Build time</th><th>JavaScript bundle</th></tr></thead><tbody>{ids.map(id=>{const c=byId[id];return <tr><td><a href={`/components/${id}/`}>{c.name}</a> <a href={c.routes.dashboard.startsWith('/benchmarks/')?`/${id}/compare/`:c.routes.dashboard}>compare</a> <a href={c.routes.dashboard.startsWith('/benchmarks/')?c.routes.dashboard:'/benchmarks/'}>benchmark</a></td><td><div class="metrics">{frameworks.map(key=><span><b>{labels[key]}</b> {ms(c.metrics.buildMs[key])}</span>)}</div></td><td><div class="metrics">{frameworks.map(key=><span><b>{labels[key]}</b> {kb(c.metrics.bundleBytes[key])}</span>)}</div></td></tr>})}</tbody></table></div></section>)}
<style>.hero{max-width:850px}.eyebrow{margin:0 0 8px;color:#64748b;font-weight:700;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:.08em;font-size:12px}.hero h1{font-size:44px;letter-spacing:-.04em;margin:0 0 10px}.hero>p:last-child,section>p{color:#64748b;line-height:1.6}.notice{border:1px solid #f59e0b;background:#fffbeb;border-radius:12px;padding:20px;margin-top:32px}.notice h2{margin-top:0}.totals{display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(4,1fr);gap:10px}.totals div{display:grid;gap:4px;padding:14px;border:1px solid #d1d5db;border-radius:10px}.totals strong{text-transform:capitalize}.totals span{font-size:13px;color:#64748b}.family,section{margin-top:38px}.family h2{font-size:20px}.table-wrap{overflow:auto;border:1px solid #d1d5db;border-radius:12px;background:white}table{width:100%;border-collapse:collapse}th,td{padding:14px 16px;border-bottom:1px solid #e5e7eb;text-align:left;vertical-align:top}th{background:#f8fafc;font-size:13px}tbody tr:last-child td{border-bottom:0}td>a{font-weight:750;color:#0759b6;text-decoration:none}.metrics{display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(2,minmax(128px,1fr));gap:6px 14px;white-space:nowrap;font-variant-numeric:tabular-nums}.metrics span{color:#64748b}.metrics b{display:inline-block;min-width:22px;color:#111827}@media(max-width:760px){.metrics,.totals{grid-template-columns:1fr}.hero h1{font-size:36px}}</style>
</Layout>
